m_q.target_metric: Count of human conflicts between 800 and 1400 AD, attributed to modern countries
sub_questions: How to extract location information from conflict names?
How to map historical locations to modern countries?
How to handle conflicts spanning multiple years?
How to attribute multi-location conflicts to countries?

schema_conflicts: Conflict column contains location information but no standardized location columns
No direct join key between conflict data and modern cities data

scale_issues: Conflict names contain location information but need parsing
Historical locations need mapping to modern countries
Some conflicts may span multiple modern countries
cross_source_conflicts: conflict_brecke.csv uses historical names, worldcities.csv uses modern country names

format_notes: Conflict column contains location information in parentheses
Century and Decade columns appear to be derived from year columns

constraints: Conflict must have StartYear and EndYear
Conflict must last at least 1 year (EndYear - StartYear >= 1)
derived_filters: Extract location names from Conflict column
Map historical locations to modern countries using worldcities.csv or external knowledge
statistical_tests: Verify century/decade calculations match year values
output_format_requirements: List of conflicts with attributed countries
